node.text:
‘Dan’and ‘Countryside’, by Julie Debray.

‘Dan’ Charcoal and conte on paper. 
"I challenged myself to draw some faces during Covid-19 and Dan was one I did in the charcoal medium; I enjoyed doing Dan and found that he and some faces were easier to work on, while others were very difficult."

‘Countryside’ Watercolor on paper.
"I find watercolor a challenging medium and I was pleased that this landscape worked well. This pastoral scene shows a big moody sky and the sunlight coming through to highlight the hill in the background while the foreground is in shadow which creates drama to the scene."

node.text:
I read a book for 2 days but I already read it for 50%. I am not someone who will keep reading if I dislike the book since I am getting busier recently. Yes... Pandemic makes me busier, I don't know why but I am grateful for it.
.
.
Anyway... The book really punches me in a super great way. I had a phone call with a friend a night before telling him that there is no way I will ever trust love or I will let myself in the position of falling in love again. But then... I read these: "You got a chance at happiness, even for a week, a month, a year? You grab it and you hold on to it for as long as it lasts." When I read those lines, there was A NAME popped-up in my head. And... What's next? Of course I GRAB MY CHANCE TO HAPPINESS!! ğŸ‰
.
.
P.S: I'll share the book I am currently reading once I finished reading it. Don't worry!

node.text: Service dogs preform a task that helps there disabled handler with there every day life. Emotional support are not service animals under the ADA.Service animals ethically should be 2-3 years of age to begging work and at least know 1 task before allowed public access in non pet friendly places. Service animals don’t have paper work or ID with in the untied states. Currently only mini horses and dogs are legally recognized as service animals by the ADA however please check with your state as different states may allow ( cats and monkeys). Service animals can not bark, pee/poop, lung, or be aggressive. They must be kept out of the way and ignored by the general public. They are not allowed in shopping carts or on tables as it a health code violation. Bringing in your pet risks the health and safety of your self and your dog and actual service handlers. HOLD UP âœ‹ğŸ¼ We have your go-to drink for the rest of summer: Mint Lemonade with Rosewater ğŸ‹ You can make it yourself with just a few ingredients!

RECIPE INSTRUCTIONS: 
• In a sauce pan, combine 2 cups water and 2 cups sugar, and simmer over low heat until the sugar has dissolved. 
• Remove from the heat, then add 1 lemon (sliced) and 1 cup of fresh mint. Let it steep for at least 30 minutes. 
• Strain out the lemon and mint, and pour the liquid into a glass container. 
• Refrigerate. 

THEN, BLEND:
• 1 cup of the liquid from above
• 1/2 cup fresh mint
• 1 lemon (sliced)
• 1/4 cup rosewater 
• 1 cup ice 
• 1 cup water 

FINALLY:
• Strain the blended liquid 
• Serve over ice
• Enjoy it on a warm day! ğŸŒ
